ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_2acc7dc7b91fd9ac3ef00b6d5ae1c598" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b410e44d45283cd6620d43a1adf37649" parent="aspace_2acc7dc7b91fd9ac3ef00b6d5ae1c598" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_4dbb8d5eeca4c4d53b010fd279fb8729" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_6ff10c10e90364b81ec5c47d4c4a5a61" parent="aspace_4dbb8d5eeca4c4d53b010fd279fb8729" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_1c8f76a6cbb01b11620230975e370137" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b612d6e38b0a339d173bac10517b0ee9" parent="aspace_1c8f76a6cbb01b11620230975e370137" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "My Notes 1980: PRO &amp; Roosevelt." CAB 120/56 - 121/741. Succinct notes of heart of documents re: French Indochina (ca. 40-50 pp.). Notebook cover headed "Cabinet Officers etc." has several pages of references to A. Creech Jones.</p><p> 2nd notebook: Rhodes Library Oxford - About 100 pp. of penciled notes on FO 371; CO 824 Register; CO 872-4-9 inclusive (1942, 1942) Mostly to FO 371/371779-90</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_882641775d4bd943c4046cce71f4aac7" level="file"><did><unittitle>DDE '54 - documents</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_67d994ea9732db56113e04a5c05d644a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_8704a27f9e9026c82100498383522608" parent="aspace_67d994ea9732db56113e04a5c05d644a" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d4c4cd2d8b44f1177511b9a1ffa9da65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Dwight D. Eisenhower Library</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_42adfae9cae0b88bcf98f8b0bf2e8c14" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives - Use of Indo China Resistance Forces</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1944/1945" type="inclusive">1944-1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_8dbabb4ee406e84827f5cd9bb4c0cdca" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b8cf794cf843366713b16e2ae2a8db23" parent="aspace_8dbabb4ee406e84827f5cd9bb4c0cdca" type="folder">10-11</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbd8f8d86f47433c2d61b3b65e326d31" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1941/1941">1941</unitdate><container id="aspace_d1a5ef3ba11fc354ddc9dca6fcfbf5e9" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_5d941ce5c62464d3db03e2817346e662" parent="aspace_d1a5ef3ba11fc354ddc9dca6fcfbf5e9" type="folder">12</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_88f942e2113e